Detailed Description

All data is passed in and out in a tagged data structure. This structure can hold a few basic data types. If you want to return a string value, you need to provide a FreeMem() entry point in your DLL so ExtendScript can free the memory after usage. Since ExtendScript does not know about the structure packing alignment, please use a pack alignment of 8. This should be OK for all 32-bit systems.
